cURL Command:
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/register -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"username":"testuser","password":"testpass"}'

Output:
{"message":"User successfully registered. Now you can login"}

Testing duplicate user registration:
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/register -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"username":"testuser","password":"testpass2"}'

Output:
{"message":"User already exists!"}

Testing registration without password:
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/register -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"username":"testuser2"}'

Output:
{"message":"Unable to register user."}
